Description: Gorgeous Fender American Standard Stratocaster with Rosewood Fret Board and Aqua Marine Metallic Body. Comes with Fender Case. I am the sole owner. Purchased in 1999 (I do not have the original receipt), has been played minimally and stored in a Fender case in a climate controlled environment. Body is in beautiful shape. No dings or chips in the paint, some very slight scratches on the back that I tried to capture in photos but seem too faint to appear. Item is priced low for the following reasons: the backplate is missing (replacement part is <$10), some slight rusting on the saddles screws (they are all still adjustable), and some discoloration/interior rusting on some of the machine heads. The two E string machine head have been replaced with regular standard Strat machine heads from another guitar I have. I will include the original american machine heads with purchase, however they do not rotate (replacement machine heads run around ~$70 a set.) Also, the handle of the case recent cracked (see photo). I haven't looked into cost of replacing this item, but it is still usable as it. The guitar has just been restrung with a set of Blue Elixir Strings, and I will include an extra set of Ernie Balls and some loose extra strings (see photo of case, which is included). Please let me know if you have any additional questions. It is a beautiful guitar, sounds amazing, and will not disappoint. Happy shopping.
Title: AMERICAN STANDARD STRATOCASTER, ROSEWOOD FINGERBOARD, AQUA MARINE METALLIC
